<title>INDIA: India Madras Cements 96/97 net down.</title>
<headline>India Madras Cements 96/97 net down.</headline>
<dateline>BOMBAY 1997-06-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year to March 31, 1997</p>
<p>	     (in million rupees unless stated)</p>
<p>    Net profit	    777.4  vs    909.0</p>
<p>    Net sales	   4,040.7  vs  3,794.6</p>
<p>    Expenditure	 2,799.4  vs  2,552.8</p>
<p>Operating profit  1,397.5  vs  1,368.1</p>
<p>    Interest		310.1  vs    193.9</p>
<p>    Gross profit	1,087.4  vs  1,174.2</p>
<p>    Depreciation	  310.0  vs    249.7</p>
<p>    Taxation		nil    vs     15.5</p>
<p>Note: Madras Cements Ltd said its board recommended a dividend of 55 percent per share. The company said taxable income being nil, the liability under minimum alternate tax would be treated as advance tax.</p>
<p>-- Bombay newsroom +91-22-265 9000</p>
